## Extending

To add a new charm library, re-run `spin new <name> --<flag>` with the additional flag (e.g. `--huh`).
To add a new command, edit `cmd/<name>/main.go` and add a new `cobra.Command` to `rootCmd`.
The template tree is composed from `_base/` (shared scaffolding), `variant_<type>/` (with every charm lib's wiring inlined behind per-lib `has<Lib>` blocks in the variant files), and the one surviving `lib/<lib>/` overlay (`lib/ai/`); see `internal/scaffold/templates/` in the spin source for the canonical set.

## Conventions

- No CGO (`CGO_ENABLED=0 go build ./...` is the smoke test).
- All charm libraries use the `charm.land/<lib>/v2` import path; v1 paths are forbidden.
- Run `task setup` once after cloning to install `gofumpt`, `goimports`, `air`, and `prism`.

## Rebuilding this file

Regenerate with: `spin new <name> <flags>` (use the same flags as the original scaffold).
